<h2 id="section-top">Ophthalmology</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="box">
<p class="module">
        This Department is managed by  
        <a href="/Services/Trusts/Overview/DefaultView.aspx?id=132456">Manchester University NHS Foundation Trust</a>
</p>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div class="service-locations clear">
<div class="panel edit-box">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<p class="address">Manchester Royal Eye Hospital Cataract Centre, First Floor, Withington Community Hospital, Nell Lane, Manchester, M20 2LR<br/>0161 2173036</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContent5af545ab52344a5ab2a5602ea4877314">
</div>
<p>The Manchester Royal Eye Hospital has a dedicated centre for treating patients with cataracts based at Withington Community Hospital. The staff from the Royal Eye Hospital travel to Withington to see patients in the friendly unit located in South Manchester.</p>
<p>The dedicated facility means that all pre-surgery checks and the cataract procedure can take place here. Patients will only attend one clinic appointment before the procedure, where they meet the team of doctors, nurses and optometrists, are assessed for surgery and have the opportunity to ask any questions.  </p>
<p>The dedicated centre provides:</p>
<ul>
<li>Safe, effective, holistic care – each patient is looked after as an individual and treatment is tailored to specific needs</li>
<li>A consultant led service provided by Manchester Royal Eye Hospital’s ophthalmic surgeons</li>
<li>Short waiting times, appointments offered 2 weeks after receiving a referral. </li>
<li>Morning or afternoon surgery sessions, available within 2 weeks from the first consultation</li>
<li>Easy access - a convenient location close to major road networks</li>
<li>Plenty of parking on site with a short walk to the front entrance</li>
<li>A positive experience - patients consistently say they would recommend our department to their friends and family </li>
</ul>
<p><strong><em>“Thank you to the staff for their kindness, consideration and effectiveness”</em></strong></p>
<p><strong><em>“thank you to the nurse that held my hand through the op and the nice cup of tea after”</em></strong></p>
<p><strong><em>“I really appreciated the way you all made me feel safe and supported throughout”</em></strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p>For more information about the cataract centre and what to expect please visit the Manchester Royal Eye Hospital website – <a href="http://www.mft.nhs.uk/royal-eye/services/cataract/">www.mft.nhs.uk/royal-eye/services/cataract/</a></p>
<p> </p></div>
</div>
